This module allows you to add, set, or clear any output header
that you specify. This is an enhanced version of the standard
"headers" module because it provides more utlities :)

This module is still under active development and not usable
yet. But feel free to go watching this repository ;)

Installation

Grab the nginx source code from nginx.net, for example, the
version 0.8.24 (see nginx compatibility), and then build the
source with this module:

    $ wget 'http://sysoev.ru/nginx/nginx-0.8.24.tar.gz'
    $ tar -xzvf nginx-0.8.24.tar.gz
    $ cd nginx-0.8.24/

    # Here we assume you would install you nginx under /opt/nginx/.
    $ ./configure --prefix=/opt/nginx \
        --add-module=/path/to/chunkin-nginx-module

    $ make -j2
    $ make install

-agentzh

